Value
A consequence of the borrowing rules is that when you have an immutable
value, you can't borrow it mutably. For example, this code won't
compile:

@verbatim
fn main() {
    let x = 5;
    let y = &mut x;
}
@end verbatim

If you tried to compile this code, you'd get the following error:

